articles.author: Kayla Williams
articles.text:
After a brutal winter that ravaged most of the United States, many of you are probably thrilled that the first day of spring is finally upon us. To celebrate the arrival of an extra hour of sunlight, blossoming flowers, and warmer weather, here are 10 strains that come in like a lion but stick with you like a lamb.
Peach Spice

Strain combination: Cotton Candy Kush and Green Queen

The sweet pear flavor in Cotton Candy Kush is balanced wonderfully by the spicy, nutty character of Green Queen.
Cherry Creamsicle

Strain combination: Vanilla Kush and Cherry Bomb

The heavier, smooth Vanilla Kush is beautifully complemented by the sweet cherry flavor of the lighter Cherry Bomb.
Strawberry Mojito

Strain combination: Strawberry Kush and Thin Mint

The unmistakable Thin Mint flavor and hybrid effects are perfectly balanced by the more physical Strawberry Kush.
Berry Tartlet

Strain combination: Blackberry Kush and Lemon Haze

These two strong flavors coupled with contrasting effects provide a balanced, memorable experience.
Banana Brush

Strain combination: Banana Kush and Durban Poison

The distinct sweetness of Banana Kush could only be matched with an earthy, uplifting flower like Durban Poison.
Blue Bayou

Strain combination: Blue Cheese and Blue Haze

Blue cheese and peppered pear is the name of the game with these two acclaimed hybrids.
Waldorf

Strain combination: SAGE and Island Sweet Skunk

The spicy sandalwood and earthy flavors of SAGE combined with Island Sweet Skunk’s buttery apple taste creates a pairing reminiscent of a classic Waldorf salad.
Rubies ‘n Roses

Strain combination: White Russian and Grapefruit

In a happy synthesis of citrus, floral, and earthy undertones, this pair provides a pleasant, invigorating lift.
Tropical Vacation

Strain combination: Pineapple Express and Cannalope Haze

Let this fruity coalescence of sweet pineapple, mango, and berry take you far, far away.
Chocolate Peel

Strain combination: Orange Kush and Chocolope

Orange and chocolate, with additional sweet and earthy undertones, make this pair a no-brainer.

articles.title: 10 Strain Pairings to Help You Celebrate Spring

articles.author: Rebecca Kelley
articles.text:
Even if you haven’t got a little Irish in ya, most everyone enjoys celebrating St. Patrick’s Day. After all, it’s an excuse to drink some Guinness, eat some soda bread and corned beef with hash, and pinch forgetful friends who aren’t wearing some hue of green today. This being Leafly, of course, we have a list of strains with a little “green” in them to help you further celebrate a fun little holiday.
Without further ado, here are 15 green-themed cannabis strains:
  1. Green Candy
Type: sativa
Top flavors: sweet, citrus, minty
Top effects: happy, euphoric, energetic
Top medical uses: pain, stress, depression
Sample review:
“One of the top 5 sativas. I always want this as part of my available medications.” – Crucian1

articles.title: Luck o' the Irish: 15 'Green' Strains to Help You Celebrate St. Patrick's Day

description: Green Queen was bred by JB Dank Nugs and is the hybrid cross of Green Crack and Space Queen. Each of these strains has exceptional standalone effects, but when combined, their speedy and heady elements work in concert to create a strain greater than the sum of its parts. Green Queen’s aroma is skunky and subtly sweet, with hints of citrus and pepper on the finish. The effects are cerebral and euphoric without being overstimulating, though expect a notable boost of physical and mental energy. This bud is deep green with bright orange pistils.

highlightedReviews.text:
First, let me state that I am very picky in what strains I medicate with.  I have tried all kinds of strains and am very specific in the effects I want to feel.  I need cannabis to 1) Calm my stomach/intestines immediately and take away nausea - and - 2) Provide me with a clear, manageable high that does NOT induce paranoia or anxiety.  

I have severe IBS, GERD and a host of other intestinal issues, so a high CBD count is important to me.  Getting so high I'm out of my head is NOT my main priority so I tend to stick to heavy, thick indicas, but I tried Green Queen per the suggestion of someone at my nearby access point.  Out of everything I have tried, this meets my needs perfectly - even better than my old favorite Romulan (which this has in it).  

It's a brilliant, clear-headed high that remains very manageable if you keep your dosage controlled.  Like anything, if you take too much, it can get pretty wild, as the THC content in this is very high, so I advise trying just a small amount the first time.  It lasts a long time - this strain has legs!  

It's the most manageable, calm, NON-NEUROTIC high I've ever experienced.  I experienced no anxiety at all, just a crisp, clean high that immediately ended my nausea and other unpleasant IBS issues.  It allowed me to function in public, in front of others, perfectly - no weird internal freak-out feeling, just a smiling, confident high.  I even feel a bit silly on it, due to the lack of anxiety.

Combine the mental clarity with the incredibly fast and powerful physical healing effects and you have what is now my new favorite strain.  I recommend this for anyone looking for a crisp, fun, manageable high, and for anyone in need of immediate physical pain relief.

Definitely what you want in a hybrid, as it seems to have aspects of both a sativa and an indica. the different aspects of the high seem to come in waves. Starts with an uplifted feeling, and a head buzz. Very mild body buzz that only seems noticeable when youre not being active. Then come the giggles, and the munchies. Damn this strain makes me eat. Great for listening to music, or dancing. On the comedown i got pretty tired and crashed hard, felt pretty groggy next day as well. Favorite strain ive tried so far

name: Green Queen
